bodyenglish:
Studio XX is looking for a new programming coordinator for September 1, 2015.

Deadline to apply: June 12, 2015 at 5pm

 

Founded in 1996, Studio XX is a bilingual feminist artist-run centre dedicated to the dissemination and production of digital arts by self-identified women, trans and gender non-conforming artists. We support creative practice at the intersection of three elements: the development of digital art from a feminist perspective and using a DIY approach. The Studio is organized in a non-hierarchical manner; the team operates using feminist values and &nbsp;principles of diversity, openness and collaboration.

JOB MANDATE

The programming coordinator is in charge of the general programming of Studio XX. They will assume development and promotion, as well as the coordination of events, of &nbsp;workshops, of the artist-in-residencies and of the biannual festival Les HTMlles, always in collaboration with the programming committee and other members of the Studio XX team.&nbsp;

TASKS

General Programming :


	Coordination of the programming committee whose mandate is to define the annual diffusion and production activities of the studio; implement tasks such as the organization of meetings, managing jury selections, etc.;
	Write calls for project proposals and regular activity reports;
	Coordination of artists and volunteers (orientation, etc.); host events and presentations (evenings and weekends);
	Monitor the budget and administrative tasks;
	Participate in grant-writing;
	Participate in the implementation of a public relations and audience development strategy as well as the artistic development of the Studio.





Biannual festival Les HTMlles&nbsp;

* Coordination of the organizing of the 2016 edition of the festival (preparation year) :


	Development of the artistic programming in collaboration with the Programming Committee;
	Organization and presentation of the festival; coordination of activities related to the event;
	Development of both a collaborative and a promotional strategy for the festival;
	Produce activity reports;
	Monitor the budget.


REPRESENTATION AND AVAILABILITY&nbsp;

The programming coordinator must be available on evenings and weekends, and be motivated to attend artistic, cultural and university events, as well as to make contacts and generally expand XX&rsquo;s network in the milieu of technological arts in order to better curate innovative and interesting programming proposals for the Studio.

QUALIFICATIONS NEEDED


	&nbsp;A strong and broad knowledge in the field of digital/technological arts;
	An understanding and interest in the complexity of feminisms;
	Experience coordinating projects;
	Excellent communicator and capable of working collaboratively with a team;
	Sense of responsibility, autonomy and initiative;
	Excellent organizational skills;
	Good knowledge of both oral and written French and English.


&nbsp;

Studio XX has non-discriminatory hiring practices and all applications will be considered.&nbsp;

Salary : 18,00 $ / hour. 25h / week * The number of hours will be scaled up in accordance with the need during the production year of Les HTMlles festival.&nbsp;

Please send your resume along with a letter of intent outlining your relevant experience for the position to emploi@studioxx.org before June 12, 2015 at 5pm.

We thank everyone in advance for submitting an application. However, only the candidates chosen for an interview will be contacted.

Interview : end of June 2015

Start date : 1 september 2015.

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

bodyfrench:
Le Studio XX est &agrave; la recherche d&#39;un-e coordonnateur-rice &agrave; la programmation dont l&#39;entr&eacute;e en fonction est pr&eacute;vue pour le 1er septembre 2015.&nbsp;

Date limite pour postuler :&nbsp;le 12 juin 2015 &agrave; 17h

 

Fond&eacute; en 1996, le Studio XX est un centre d&rsquo;artistes autog&eacute;r&eacute; bilingue et f&eacute;ministe d&eacute;di&eacute; au soutien &agrave; la production et &agrave; la diffusion des artistes s&rsquo;auto-identifiant comme femmes, trans et dissident-e-s en arts num&eacute;riques. Nous soutenons la cr&eacute;ation au croisement de trois id&eacute;es : le d&eacute;veloppement des arts num&eacute;riques sous une perspective f&eacute;ministe et dans une approche DIY (artisanale). Le Studio est organis&eacute; de mani&egrave;re non-hi&eacute;rarchique; l&rsquo;&eacute;quipe travaille selon des valeurs f&eacute;ministes et des principes de diversit&eacute;, d&rsquo;ouverture et de collaboration.

MANDAT DU POSTE

Le-la coordonnateur-rice &agrave; la programmation est en charge de la programmation g&eacute;n&eacute;rale du Studio XX. Il-Elle assume son d&eacute;veloppement et sa promotion, ainsi que la coordination des &eacute;v&eacute;nements, des ateliers, des r&eacute;sidences d&rsquo;artistes et du festival biennal Les HTMlles, en collaboration avec le comit&eacute; de programmation de l&rsquo;organisme et les autres membres de l&rsquo;&eacute;quipe.

T&Acirc;CHES

Programmation g&eacute;n&eacute;rale :


	Coordination du comit&eacute; de programmation dont le mandat est de d&eacute;finir la programmation annuelle du centre concernant les activit&eacute;s de diffusion et de production; mise en oeuvre des t&acirc;ches li&eacute;es au comit&eacute; (organisation des r&eacute;unions, gestion des jurys de s&eacute;lection, etc.);
	R&eacute;daction d&rsquo;appels &agrave; projets et de rapports d&rsquo;activit&eacute;s r&eacute;guliers;
	Coordination des artistes et des b&eacute;n&eacute;voles (accueil, etc.); pr&eacute;sentation des &eacute;v&eacute;nements de diffusion du centre (certains soirs et fins de semaine);
	Veille budg&eacute;taire et suivi administratif;
	Participation &agrave; la r&eacute;daction des demandes de subventions;
	Participation &agrave; la mise en oeuvre d&rsquo;une strat&eacute;gie de relations publiques et de d&eacute;veloppement des publics ainsi qu&rsquo;au d&eacute;veloppement artistique du Studio.


Le festival Les HTMlles
* Il s&rsquo;agit de coordonner l&rsquo;organisation de l&rsquo;&eacute;dition 2016 du festival (ann&eacute;e de pr&eacute;paration) :


	&Eacute;laboration de la programmation artistique en collaboration avec le comit&eacute; de programmation;
	Organisation et pr&eacute;sentation du festival; coordination des activit&eacute;s reli&eacute;es &agrave; l&rsquo;&eacute;v&eacute;nement;
	&Eacute;laboration de la strat&eacute;gie collaborative et promotionnelle du festival;
	Production de rapports d&rsquo;activit&eacute;s;
	Veille budg&eacute;taire.


REPR&Eacute;SENTATION ET DISPONIBILIT&Eacute;
L&rsquo;employ&eacute;-e doit faire preuve de curiosit&eacute; et &ecirc;tre disponible &agrave; l&rsquo;occasion les soir&eacute;es et les fins de semaine afin d&rsquo;assister &agrave; des &eacute;v&eacute;nements artistiques, culturels, universitaires et de r&eacute;seautage, de cr&eacute;er des contacts et de demeurer &agrave; l&rsquo;aff&ucirc;t des activit&eacute;s du milieu artistique dans lequel l&rsquo;organisme &eacute;volue, et ce dans l&rsquo;optique d&rsquo;alimenter des propositions de programmation novatrices et int&eacute;ressantes.

QUALIFICATIONS RECHERCH&Eacute;ES


	Solides connaissances dans le domaine des arts num&eacute;riques;
	Compr&eacute;hension et int&eacute;r&ecirc;t pour les probl&eacute;matiques f&eacute;ministes;
	Exp&eacute;rience en coordination de projets;
	Capacit&eacute; &agrave; communiquer et &agrave; travailler en &eacute;quipe;
	Sens des responsabilit&eacute;s, esprit d&rsquo;initiative et autonomie;
	Excellent sens de l&rsquo;organisation;
	Bonne connaissance orale et &eacute;crite du fran&ccedil;ais et de l&rsquo;anglais.


Le Studio XX proc&egrave;de &agrave; des pratiques d&rsquo;embauche non-discriminatoires : toute candidature est admise.

Salaire : 18,00 $ / l&#39;heure. 25h / semaine * Le nombre d&rsquo;heures sera ajust&eacute; (&agrave; la hausse) lors de l&rsquo;ann&eacute;e de production du festival Les HTMlles.

Veuillez faire parvenir votre curriculum vitae accompagn&eacute; d&rsquo;une lettre d&rsquo;intention d&eacute;crivant vos exp&eacute;riences pertinentes pour le poste &nbsp;&agrave; emploi @ studioxx.org &nbsp;avant le 12 juin 2015 &agrave; 17h. (Des r&eacute;f&eacute;rences seront demand&eacute;es au besoin).

Nous remercions &agrave; l&rsquo;avance toutes les personnes qui nous soumettront leur candidature. Cependant, seul-e-s les candidat-e-s retenu-e-s pour une entrevue seront contact&eacute;-e-s.&nbsp;

Entrevues d&#39;embauche : fin juin 2015.&nbsp;

Entr&eacute;e en fonction : Le 1er septembre 2015.

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

